lu.uni.geko.util.datastructures
Interface N2NMap<K,V>

Type Parameters:
K - the key type (the domain of the mapping)
V - the value type (the image of the mapping)
All Known Subinterfaces:
BiN2NMap<K,V>
All Known Implementing Classes:
BiHashN2NMap, HashN2NMap
public interface N2NMap<K,V>

A mapping from possibly multiple keys to possibly multiple values. A Map<Set<K>, Set<V>> can be regarded as equivalent to a N2NMap<K, V> but does not offer convenient methods, caching and synchronisation.

Whereas instances of Map<K, V> should be named key2ValueMap, instances of Mapping<K,V> should be named key2ValuesN2NMap (with an s after Value to emphasise that we map on possibly multiple elements). Note that we differentiate between the words mapping, Map, N2NMap in order to distinguish between the concept of a mapping and the implementation of its 1to1 and NtoN variant.
